        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down. | Bromley. | Kent. | S.E.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>April. 24<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>Dear Oliver.</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>Many thanks for Oxalis; of 38 flowers sent 24 are long-styled &amp; 14 short-styled, just as in the flowers here; but whether this depends on mere useless variability or on useful dimorphism, I suspect experiment will alone show:<ref target="#foot.f2"/> I have got plants in pots for next spring.</p>
<p>I am quite aware the other æstival flower is a very much more curious case. I return 6<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> stamp which I suppose is a Kew affair.—</p>
<p>Yours very sincerely | C. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
                <div type="tnotes">
                    <note xml:id="tnote.n1">1.3 useful] <hi rend="italic">interl</hi></note>
                </div>

            
            
